%description:

Tests the DHCPINFORM client-side gateway sanity check. The client runs in
informMode with an externally configured address (192.168.1.50/24), but the
server is configured to hand out a router (default gateway) option that lies
outside the client's local subnet (10.0.0.1). A default-route gateway must be
directly reachable on the local subnet, so the client must reject the
off-link gateway with a warning and must NOT install a default route.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = Test
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "[%t %M] "
sim-time-limit = 60s

**.app[*].cmdenv-log-level = detail

*.client.eth[0].address = "AA-00-00-00-00-0A"

*.configurator.config = xml("<config> \
        <interface hosts='server' address='192.168.1.1' netmask='255.255.255.0'/> \
        <interface hosts='client' address='192.168.1.50' netmask='255.255.255.0'/> \
        </config>")

*.server.numApps = 1
*.server.app[0].typename = "DhcpServer"
*.server.app[0].numReservedAddresses = 100
*.server.app[0].maxNumClients = 5
*.server.app[0].gateway = "10.0.0.1"
*.server.app[0].leaseTime = 1000s

*.client.numApps = 1
*.client.app[0].typename = "DhcpClient"
*.client.app[0].informMode = true

%file: test.ned

import inet.test.moduletest.lib.*;
import inet.node.ethernet.Eth10M;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetSwitch;
import inet.node.inet.StandardHost;
import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv4.Ipv4NetworkConfigurator;

network Test
{
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv4NetworkConfigurator;
        switch: EthernetSwitch;
        server: StandardHost;
        client: StandardHost;
    connections:
        server.ethg++ <--> Eth10M <--> switch.ethg++;
        client.ethg++ <--> Eth10M <--> switch.ethg++;
}

%# The exchange must still complete normally.
%contains: stdout
DHCPINFORM completed; local configuration parameters applied without acquiring a lease.

%# The off-subnet gateway must be detected and rejected.
%contains: stdout
DHCPINFORM ACK gateway 10.0.0.1 is not on the locally configured subnet 192.168.1.50/255.255.255.0; ignoring it (not installing a default route).

%# Therefore no default route is installed (the accept-path log must not appear).
%not-contains: stdout
DHCPINFORM ACK router (default gateway):

%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
